The paper focuses on accelerating deep convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of graphics processing units (GPUs) also suggests a potential fit for the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new algorithm for low-precision quantized Winograd convolution, which could be relevant to the neural networks (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
